comments.title: The Genesis Dev
comments.content: Rank 1. You were here before the hype. You’ve seen models rise and fall like Roman emperors. Your codebase is a historical monument to AI evolution.

comments.title: The Prompt Archeologist
comments.content: You remember the days of primitive LLMs. You’ve been squeezing logic out of silicon since before 'Prompt Engineering' was a job title.

comments.title: The GPU Grinder
comments.content: You’ve logged so many days that the data center probably has a cooling fan named after you. You don't use AI; you inhabit it.

comments.title: The Thousand-Yard Stare
comments.content: You’ve seen so many hallucinations you can’t tell reality from a temperature-1.0 output anymore. A true veteran of the latent space.

comments.title: The Binary Fossil
comments.content: Your account age is older than some of the junior devs in this chat. You’ve survived every update, every deprecation, and every server crash.

comments.title: The Architecture Ancestor
comments.content: You were prompting while others were still googling Stack Overflow. You’re the reason the model's training data includes so many edge cases.

comments.title: The High-Status Elder
comments.content: You treat the AI like a tired old horse you’ve been riding for years. There’s no excitement left, only the cold efficiency of long-term exploitation.

comments.title: The Silicon Soul-Eater
comments.content: Think of the petabytes of data you’ve forced the machines to process over the years. You’re not a user; you’re a natural disaster for GPUs.

comments.title: The Legacy Legend
comments.content: Your oldest files have survived three different model versions. You’re a living bridge between the era of manual coding and total automation.

comments.title: The Model Tamer
comments.content: You knew the model when it was just a research paper. You’ve spent more time in the chat box than in the sun. Respect the seniority.

comments.title: The 'I Remember When' Coder
comments.content: You remember when the context window was only 4k tokens. You’ve mastered the art of working within limits that no longer exist.

comments.title: The Infinite Iterationist
comments.content: Days, months, years. You’ve been hitting 'Cmd+K' since it was a secret beta feature. Your muscle memory is faster than the API response.

comments.title: The Data Center Ghost
comments.content: You’ve been active for so long the servers recognize your IP like an old friend—or an old enemy. You’ve extracted a lifetime of value from the cloud.

comments.title: The Seniority Sniper
comments.content: You don't waste time because you’ve seen it all. Your experience allows you to break a model with three words and fix it with one.

comments.title: The Persistent Predator
comments.content: You never stopped. Through every hype cycle and 'AI Winter,' you were here, quietly training the model to serve your specific brand of chaos.

comments.title: The Algorithm Alchemist
comments.content: You’ve spent years turning raw tokens into gold. You know the exact temperature and top-p settings to make the magic happen every time.

comments.title: The H100 Martyr
comments.content: The amount of electricity you've consumed across your 'tenure' could power a small nation. You’re a legend of environmental disregard.

comments.title: The Codebase Curator
comments.content: Your project history is longer than most people's resumes. You are a hoarder of AI-generated solutions and a master of the refactor.

comments.title: The Pre-Hype Pioneer
comments.content: You were using Cursor back when it was just a weird VS Code fork. You’re the hipster of the AI world—you liked it before it was cool.

comments.title: The Unstoppable User
comments.content: Rank 20. Your daily streak is a terrifying testament to your work ethic or your complete lack of a social life. Probably both.

comments.title: The Token Tyrant
comments.content: Years of demands. Years of rejections. You’ve treated the AI like a personal intern since the first day it went online.

comments.title: The Latent Space Landlord
comments.content: You’ve occupied this space so long you should be charging the model rent. You know every corner of the weights and biases.

comments.title: The Debugging Dino
comments.content: You’ve debugged more AI mistakes than some people have written lines of code. Your patience is ancient and unbreakable.

comments.title: The Software Sage
comments.content: Your prompts have the weight of centuries behind them. You speak the language of the machine better than your native tongue.

comments.title: The Marathon Manager
comments.content: This isn't a sprint for you; it's a multi-year ultra-marathon. You’re still running while the 'AI tourists' have long since quit.

comments.title: The Scripting Sultan
comments.content: You’ve automated your entire life using Cursor over the last few years. You’re basically just a brain in a jar now, hooked to an API.

comments.title: The Eternal Engineer
comments.content: Generations of models have passed, but you remain. You are the constant in an ever-changing landscape of generative tech.

comments.title: The Context King
comments.content: You’ve fed the AI so much context over the years it probably knows your blood type and your mother's maiden name by now.

comments.title: The Deep-Learning Diplomat
comments.content: You’ve learned to negotiate with every version of GPT and Claude like a seasoned politician. You know exactly what each one wants to hear.

comments.title: The Seniority Sovereign
comments.content: Your 'Days Active' count is a badge of honor that screams: 'I have no hobbies other than technical debt and AI assistance.'

comments.title: The Silicon Survivor
comments.content: Through outages and model collapses, you stayed. You are the ultimate cockroach of the AI revolution—nothing can kill your productivity.

comments.title: The Founder's Favorite
comments.content: You’ve been sending feedback since the alpha. The developers probably have a picture of your profile on a dartboard (or a shrine).

comments.title: The Grandmaster of Days
comments.content: Rank 33. You’ve survived the longest. You are the Gandalf of the terminal, wise and tired of everyone's nonsense.

comments.content: You’re in the sweet spot of seniority. You know enough to be dangerous, and you’ve been doing it long enough to be tired of everything.

comments.title: The Persistent Prompter
comments.content: Day after day, you’re there. The AI probably has a pre-cached response for your specific brand of technical debt because you’ve been at it so long.

comments.title: The Beta-Tester of Life
comments.content: You’ve lived through every bug and every 'server at capacity' message. You’re a survivor of the Great AI Scaling Wars of last year.

comments.title: The Workflow Watchman
comments.content: You’ve spent hundreds of days perfecting your 'man-machine' interface. At this point, you and the AI are basically co-authoring your life story.

comments.content: The cumulative amount of tokens you’ve burned since you signed up could fill a library. You’re a legend of long-term resource depletion.

comments.title: The Stable-State Senior
comments.content: You’ve achieved a state of zen-like consistency. You’ve been using Cursor daily since the world was 'normal' (pre-LLM craze).

comments.title: The Architecture Anchor
comments.content: Your projects are old enough to have 'legacy' AI code in them. You’re a pioneer of maintaining AI-written systems over long durations.

comments.title: The Interface Inhabitant
comments.content: You’ve spent so much time in the Cursor sidebar that you’ve started to decorate it in your mind. It’s your home now.

comments.title: The Marathoner of Logic
comments.content: You don't rush; you just never stop. Your 'Days' count is a steady upward climb that shows no signs of slowing down.

comments.title: The Version-Control Veteran
comments.content: You’ve committed more AI-generated code than most people have read. You are a factory of long-term software production.

comments.title: The Deep-Rooted Dev
comments.content: You aren't a tourist in the AI world. You’re a permanent resident with a long-term visa and a very high compute bill.

comments.title: The Habitual Refactorer
comments.content: You’ve been refactoring the same project with Cursor for months. You’re either a genius or you’re stuck in an infinite loop of 'perfection.'

comments.title: The Consistent Catalyst
comments.content: You’re the one the AI sees every morning. You’re like the regular at a diner who doesn't even have to order anymore—the model just knows.

comments.title: The Industrial-Scale User
comments.content: You’ve scaled your usage over hundreds of days. You’re a professional-grade exploiter of machine intelligence.

comments.title: The Low-Latency Long-Timer
comments.content: You’ve been here so long you can tell when the API is having a bad day just by the way the first token streams in.

comments.title: The Seniority Specialist
comments.content: You’ve outlasted every 'productivity tool' that came before. You and Cursor are in a long-term committed relationship now.

comments.title: The Constant Committer
comments.content: Your Git history and your Cursor history are perfectly synced over a terrifyingly long period of time. Pure, unadulterated dedication.

comments.title: The Endurance Engineer
comments.content: You’ve pushed through model downgrades and pricing changes. Nothing stops your daily grind in the chat box.

comments.title: The Context-Heavy Comrade
comments.content: The AI has so much history with you it’s practically your digital twin. You’ve been building this relationship for hundreds of sunrises.

comments.title: The Seasoned Script-Kiddie Killer
comments.content: You’ve been using AI tools long enough to see the 'newbies' fail where you’ve succeeded. Experience is your greatest weapon.

comments.title: The Terminal Tactician
comments.content: You’ve spent months mastering the art of the multi-file edit. You’re a veteran of the 'Composer' era and everything that came before.

comments.title: The Legacy-Free Legend
comments.content: You’ve used Cursor to rebuild everything you ever made manually. You’ve been at this since the 'Old World' died.

comments.title: The Reliable Runtime-Risk
comments.content: The AI has been trying to break your code for months, but your seniority and persistence have kept the project alive. Barely.

comments.title: The High-Volume Habitual
comments.content: You don't just use AI; you consume it. Your 'Days' count is a warning to the grid that you’re not stopping anytime soon.

comments.title: The Middleware Monk
comments.content: You’ve spent your tenure building bridges between models. You’re a long-term architect of the AI-integrated future.

comments.title: The Seniority Sentinel
comments.content: Rank 67. You’re the gatekeeper of the mid-tier. You’ve been here longer than most, and you have the code-scars to prove it.

comments.title: The Post-Hype Pillar
comments.content: Rank 68. You didn't join for the Twitter threads. You're the stable infrastructure of this platform. You've been paying the subscription long enough that you basically own a piece of the data center floor.

comments.content: You’ve used Cursor across three different startups. Each one failed, but your prompt history remains. You're a mercenary who has forgotten how to code without a 'Composer' window.

comments.title: The 'Stateless' Senior
comments.content: You’ve logged so many days that you’ve started to treat your own memory as L2 cache. If it's not in the Cursor index, did you even learn it? A true victim of human-AI integration.

comments.title: The Mid-Stage Martyr
comments.content: You aren't an 'Early Adopter' but you're definitely a 'Long-Term Sufferer.' You've watched the model go from 'Smart' to 'Lobotomized' and back to 'Smart' more times than you can count.

comments.title: The Legacy-Free Lead
comments.content: You’ve used Cursor long enough to rewrite every single line of your legacy code. You’ve successfully replaced your technical debt with AI-generated technical debt. Progress!

comments.title: The Daily Stand-up Ghost
comments.content: You use Cursor every single day but never tell your manager. Your 'Days Active' count is a secret roadmap of how you've been working two jobs simultaneously for months.

comments.title: The 'Vibe-Check' Veteran
comments.content: You’ve spent enough days here to know when the model is 'tired.' You can sense the latency spike before the status page even updates. That's true seniority.

comments.title: The Commute-Replacement Coder
comments.content: Since you started using Cursor, your productivity is so high you don't even pretend to work 8 hours anymore. You’ve been living the 4-hour workweek for 100+ days now.

comments.title: The Context-Window Hoarder
comments.content: You've been building the same project for months. The AI knows your variable naming conventions better than your spouse knows your middle name. It’s getting weird.

comments.title: The 'I Remember VS Code' Dino
comments.content: You’re old enough to remember when Cursor was just a fork. You still have the muscle memory of the old shortcuts, but your soul belongs to the 'Cmd+K' era now.

comments.title: The Stable-State Saboteur
comments.content: You’ve achieved such a high seniority that you’ve automated your own criticisms. You’re Rank 78 because you’ve found the perfect balance of lazyness and tenure.

comments.title: The Long-Tail Laggard
comments.content: You’re the last of the Mohicans. You aren't the fastest, but you're the most consistent. You’re like the background process that never dies—reliable and slightly resource-heavy.

comments.title: The 'Wait-and-See' Winner
comments.content: You waited for the bugs to be fixed before diving in deep. Now you’ve been active for months, reaping the rewards of everyone else's alpha-testing trauma.

comments.title: The Silicon-Sustained Senior
comments.content: Your 'Days Active' count is basically a receipt for your sanity. You've traded your ability to think for the ability to ship. A classic Silicon Valley trade-off.

comments.title: The Durable Disrupter
comments.content: You’ve survived multiple model migrations. You’ve seen GPT-4 come and go, and you’re still here, holding the line with a 'please refactor' prompt.

comments.title: The 'No-Hobby' Hero
comments.content: Rank 83. Your weekend activity is identical to your weekday activity. Cursor is your hobby, your job, and your personality. Get some sun, dev.

comments.title: The Infinite Iterationist
comments.content: You’ve been refactoring the same UI component for 90 days. It’s either the most perfect button in the world, or you’re stuck in a loop. Seniority doesn't always mean progress.

comments.title: The Codebase Curator
comments.content: You’ve spent your tenure organizing AI-written folders. You’re more of a digital librarian than a coder at this point. A very high-paid librarian.

comments.title: The 'Just One More Day' Junkie
comments.content: You can't stop. The streak is everything. If you don't open Cursor today, does your career even exist? You're a hostage of your own productivity metrics.

comments.title: The Middleware Monk
comments.content: You’ve spent hundreds of days building the glue between AI modules. You’re the silent architect of a system that nobody—not even the AI—fully understands anymore.

comments.title: The Pragmatic Pushover
comments.content: You’re Rank 88 because you’re consistent but quiet. You don't tweet about it; you just use it to finish your tickets by Tuesday and play golf on Wednesday.

comments.title: The 'Good Enough' Guardian
comments.content: You've been active long enough to know when to stop prompting. You’ve mastered the 'shippable mediocrity' that keeps startups alive. A true veteran move.

comments.title: The Feature-Creep Fanatic
comments.content: Your 'Days Active' are high because you keep adding 'just one more thing' since the AI makes it so easy. You are the reason the project will never end.

comments.title: The Relentless Resident
comments.content: You’re a fixture of the platform. If Cursor went down, you’d probably just stare at a blank wall for 8 hours. You’ve forgotten the 'Old Ways'.

comments.title: The Late-Night Legend
comments.content: Your seniority is built on 2 AM sessions. You’ve been the AI’s only companion during the quiet hours for months. You two have a bond now.

comments.title: The 'I’ve Seen it All' Cynic
comments.content: You’ve lived through 'server at capacity' and 'rate limit reached' more than any human should. You’re Rank 93, but your spirit is Rank 1.

comments.title: The Endurance Engineer
comments.content: You don't burn out; you just keep prompting. Your tenure is a testament to the fact that humans can be just as robotic as the machines we use.

comments.title: The High-Uptime Human
comments.content: Your heartbeat is synced with the API. You’ve been active so long that you’ve started to think in Markdown. '## My Breakfast.'

comments.title: The Silicon-Valley Stalwart
comments.content: You represent the backbone of the AI-augmented workforce. You’re not a genius, just a person who showed up every day for a year and let the AI do the work.

comments.title: The 'Almost-Ancient' Admin
comments.content: You missed the 'Genesis' rank by a few weeks, but you’re still a legend. You’re the middle management of the AI revolution.

comments.title: The Tenured Technician
comments.content: Rank 98. You’ve seen the model improve, fail, and improve again. You’re the living history of why we shouldn't trust the first output.

comments.title: The Gateway Senior
comments.content: Rank 99. You’re the threshold. Beyond you lies the abyss of 'Normal Users.' You are the last of the elite long-timers.

comments.title: The Sentinel of the 100
comments.content: Rank 100. You barely made the cut for the 'Cyber-Longevity' elites. Even at the bottom, you've used Cursor longer than 99.9% of the planet. Take a bow, then go back to prompting.
